        <h3 id="what_is_front_end" class="mt-4">➥ What Is Front-End </h3>
        
        <div>
            <p>The front end , also called <b> client side </b>of a web application , is everything that the <b> user sees and interacts</b> within inside their browser. It includes everything the user experiences directly: from text and colors to buttons, images etc. The main purpose of the client side is to collect data from users.
            </p>
    
            <h6 class="mt-4 fw-semibold">The front end is built with 3 key technologies : </h6>
    
            <ul>
                <li>
                   <b> HTML (HyperText Markup Language):</b> <br>
                        It  is the backbone of the Web. Every website you visit is built with HTML. It takes care of 
                        all the structure and content
    
                </li>
                <li><b> CSS (Cascading Style Sheets):</b> <br>
                    It is what controls the look and feel of the page. CSS sets the colors, fonts, Background
                    And  the way is page laid out
                    </li>
                <li><b> JavaScript:</b> <br>
                    It is a programming language commonly 
                   used to create interactive effects within web browsers.
                </li>
            </ul>

        </div>

        <!-- ====================================================================================================================================== -->

        <h3 id="what_is_backend" class="mt-4">➥ What Is Back End </h3>
        
        <div>
            <p>Back-end development refers to the <b> server-side </b>development. It is the term used for the <b> behind-the-scenes</b> activities that happen 
                When performing any action on a web application. <br> Backend developer focuses on databases, business logic, and the architecture of web application.
            </p>
            <p>Think for a minute,  what happens when you fill your username and password in Gmail’s login page. </p>
    
            <ul>
                <li>All the data you filled goes to the gmail server</li>
                <li>At the server , there is some piece of code which receives this data , performs a search query on the database and retrieves the result.</li>
                <li>  Based on the result of the query , it sends the response login accepted or login failed to the browser.
                </li>
                <li>And the browser displays this result to you.</li>
            </ul>
    
            <h6 class="mt-4 fw-semibold">A backend developer needs to understand 2 very important elements : </h6>

            <ol>
                <li>A server side programming language like Python , Java, PHP , Ruby, C# , Node JS etc
                </li>
                <li>Database Management System like Oracle, MySQL, MongoDB  etc.
                </li>
            </ol>

            <div class="web_img_container">
                <img class="web_img_responsive" src="/blog-img/web3.png" alt="">
            </div>
            
            <h6 class="mt-4 fw-semibold" >What Full Stack Web Development Contains?</h6>

            <p>Full stack developers work with both the front and back end of a web application. They’re familiar with HTML, CSS, JavaScript and one or more backend language/framework which can be JEE or Django or Node JS
            </p>

        </div>

        <hr style="border-top: 2px solid #5c5c5c;" >

        <!-- ===================================================================================================================================== -->
        
        <h3 id="what_is_library" class="mt-4">➥ What Is A Library </h3>
        
        <div>
            <p>A collection of predefined methods ,classes or Interfaces used for solving common problems.
            Come either bundled with a language or can be downloaded from
                the internet & used.</p>

            <h6 class="mt-4 fw-semibold" >Benefits Of Library :</h6>
            <ul>
                <li>Reusability </li>
                <li>Reduces programmer’s efforts</li>
                <li>Allows a programmer to focus on main 
                    problem</li>
            </ul>
    
            <h6  class="mt-4 fw-semibold">A Real Life Example </h6>
            <div class="left_border_design">
                <p>Imagine , a chef needs to bake a Pizza . Think , how he would go for it ? </p>
                <p>Prepare a dough ➦ Stretch it using rolling pin ➦ Cut  it using pizza cutter ➦ Bake it in an oven ➦ Job done! ➦ These tools(knife , rolling pin ,oven) are like a library </p>
            </div>
    
            <h6 class="mt-4 fw-semibold">Some of the JavaScript Libraries are :</h6>
            <ul>
                <li>React JS</li>
                <li>jQuery</li>
                <li>DOJO toolkit</li>
                <li>Vue.js</li>
                <li>Numeral.js</li>
            </ul>
    
            <!-- ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- -->
    
            <h5  class="mt-4 fw-semibold">Conclusion</h5>
            <p>Web development is a vast and dynamic field that is continuously growing , So to keep up with the pace it is essential to keep learning . Upgrading your skills in these crucial time will make you reach your goal . Since web development is a vast field , it doesnot matter whether you want to be a front-end or Back-end developer only learning and staying focused will keep you moving . From tutorials to courses , developers to communitites there are many resources available online . So choose what you want to be and stay inspired , keep coding and never stop your journey .</p>
        </div>

